<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1399,750,1133]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName authority="G. Kirchn., Arboretum Muscaviense" authorityName="G. Kirchn., Arboretum Muscaviense" box="[189,976,750,777]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Carpinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="betulus" variety="heterophylla">
<emphasis box="[189,315,750,777]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">C. betulus</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[385,532,750,776]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">heterophylla</emphasis>
G.Kirchn., 
<emphasis box="[685,976,750,776]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Arboretum Muscaviense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 667 (
<bibRefCitation author="Petzold E. C. A. &amp; Kirchner G." box="[1064,1386,750,777]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref43493" refString="Petzold E. C. A. &amp; Kirchner G. 1864. Arboretum Muscaviense. W. Opetz, Gotha. Available from: https: // books. google. de / books? id = a 5 UCAAAAYAAJ [accessed: 1 Jul. 2015]." type="url" year="1864">Petzold &amp; Kirchner 1864</bibRefCitation>
). – 
<taxonomicName box="[260,383,786,812]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Carpinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="betulus">
<emphasis box="[260,383,786,812]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">C. betulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
f. 
<emphasis box="[423,570,786,812]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">heterophylla</emphasis>
(G.Kirchn.) K.Koch, 
<emphasis box="[840,987,786,812]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Dendrologie</emphasis>
2 (2): 3 (
<bibRefCitation author="Koch K. H. E." box="[1111,1251,786,812]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref40942" refString="Koch K. H. E. 1873. Dendrologie; Baume, Straucher und Halbstraucher, welche in Mittel- und Nord- Europa im Freien kultivirt werden. Vol. 2. F. Enke, Erlangen. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 20459" type="book" year="1873">Koch 1873</bibRefCitation>
). – Original citation: No detailed data given. – 
<typeStatus box="[625,688,822,848]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Type</typeStatus>
: not localized. – Note: Kirchner gave the name “ 
<emphasis box="[1238,1385,821,847]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">heterophylla</emphasis>
” to plants that have both normal-shaped leaves and deeply serrated leaves, regardless whether the leaf serration is of the ‘Incisa’ or ‘Quercifolia’ 
<typeStatus box="[748,801,893,919]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">type</typeStatus>
, which he regarded as synonymous, as did Koch. As the mutation occurs spontaneously and may be fixed by cuttings, this name ‘Heterophylla’ is complicated to use. Kirchner refers to “Bth. cat.”, meaning the catalogue of James Booth and Söhne nursery in Klein-Flottbek, 
<collectingRegion box="[544,657,1000,1026]" country="Germany" name="Hamburg" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Hamburg</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[668,779,1000,1026]" name="Germany" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Germany</collectingCountry>
. As there is no reference to Loudon, Kirchner’s name cannot be regarded as a clear recombination of 
<taxonomicName authority="hort. ex Loudon" authorityName="Loudon" box="[791,1315,1035,1062]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Carpinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="betulus" variety="heterophylla">
<emphasis box="[791,911,1035,1062]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">C. betulus</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[969,1116,1035,1061]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">heterophylla</emphasis>
hort. ex Loudon
</taxonomicName>
, which is an invalid name published as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[778,897,1071,1097]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Carpinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="betulus">
<emphasis box="[778,897,1071,1097]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">C. betulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
‘Quercifolia’. Therefore, Kirchner’s name is not illegitimate, but rather a later homonym.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
